Description:
Secluded Country Lifestyle 6.5 acres 2.63ha approx.
This perfectly positioned rural holding in the sought after Gnarwarre area, blends an outstanding country lifestyle while located within an easy commute of Geelong, Highton Village, Ring Road, Deakin University, Epworth Hospital and the Waurn Ponds Shopping Centre.
Set on approximately 6.5 acres and surrounded by a tranquil garden setting this immaculately presented family residence is set well back from the road and is enhanced by the mature stand of trees lining the driveway.
The brick veneer home with solar electricity comprises four bedrooms, master with walk in robe and ensuite, open plan living and dining with split system, kitchen with double oven, induction hot plates and dishwasher, formal lounge and dining also with split system, study, central bathroom and laundry.
Externally there is a two bay machinery shed and workshop with power and water, four main paddocks including horse paddock with shelter, chook pen, fruit trees, vegie garden, dam and approximately 70,000 litres of tank water.
This property is well suited to those wishing to live close to facilities but enjoy a beautiful country setting making this your perfect lifestyle change.

Description:
Charm, Style & Character
Featuring a sophisticated renovation, this gorgeous weatherboard home is a charming blend of original and new. Immaculately presented, in a highly desired location, this home will capture your eye from the moment you step through the door.
Greeted with a wide entry hall and beautiful high ceilings showcasing the elegance that is displayed throughout. A formal living and separate dining area positioned at the front of the home, with original features including an ornamental fireplace, beautifully captures the charm of the home.
The stunning open plan kitchen features gas stove top, caesar stone bench tops and an abundance of storage. The kitchen adjoins the second living area, making this space perfect for family living.
French doors seamlessly adjoin the living area to the generous backyard. Outside, a perfectly manicured lawn with an impressive outdoor patio provides a great space for the entertainment of family and friends.
Convenient double rear street entry from Thear street, including a single car garage with built in shelves and a handy workshop space. A separate wide entry allows the ideal space for storage of a caravan, boat or trailer.
This family home consists of four spacious bedrooms, two with BIRs. The master bedroom with an ensuite.
A good-sized family bathroom featuring European laundry.
Find yourself conveniently located within close proximity to East Geelong shops, Geelong CBD and the waterfront. With everything East Geelong has to offer, be prepared to fall in love with this home the moment you walk through the front door.
Other features:
- Ducted heating
- Reverse cycle cooling
- Inbuilt outdoor fenced spa
- Upstairs study.

Description:
Modern family home on 767m2 (approx.).
Built just 10 years ago, this home is in immaculate condition and offers 25 squares of living (including garage) and is set on a massive 767m2 (approx.) allotment in a wide, low traffic street.
Positioned 5 minutes to the CBD, train station, schools and shops, a short walk to the show grounds, local reserves and Barwon River, the location is unbeatable for value.
Western Breakwater is a tightly held niche suburb of approximately 200 homes with the majority privately owned by long term residents.
With the average house price of the 2 most immediate neighbouring suburbs of East Geelong and South Geelong being 67% higher and 72% higher respectively as of March 2019, this is arguably the best value and most underrated location in Geelong.
The home was built with all the modern conveniences and boasts a functional layout incorporating open space and natural light. A large entry way is tiled and leads all the way through into the heart of the home. Comprising 4 bedrooms, master with ensuite and walk in robe, 2 generous living areas, open plan kitchen /meals, central bathroom, separate toilet and laundry, this home covers all the family needs.
The chef of the home will enjoy the modern kitchen that provides full view of the main activity centre and boasts stainless appliances, stone tops, double drawer dishwasher, double pantry, plenty of bench space and a breakfast bar.
Climate is controlled year round by ducted gas heating and evaporative cooling throughout, whilst energy bills are practically eliminated by a 4KW team of solar panels.
Outside, you will NOT be left wanting for space. A massive rear yard with very low maintenance needs includes a paved entertainment space and loads of open grass area giving you plenty of room for the kids and pets and many options to add your stamp and make it your own.
Take advantage to secure one of the best value homes available in the market place and call Dion today on 0424 940 629 to learn more.

Description:
Possibilities Galore in East Geelong!
This neat much loved family property is ideally located in a quiet court in lovely East Geelong and is close to the Botanical Gardens, the Geelong Waterfront, East Shopping area and the city. Sitting on an impressive 997m2 parcel of land it has almost unlimited possibilities. For the first home buyer it is a great entry point for this sought after suburb, for the renovator it offers room to extend and enhance and for the developer it has the potential to demolish and built numerous townhouses (STCA).
The home comprises three bedrooms, lounge, immaculate kitchen/dinette, neat central bathroom, separate laundry and ample storage. Features include convection gas heater, Axminster carpets and air-conditioner. A two car garage and huge rear yard round off a very attractive package. This really is a once in a lifetime opportunity to buy a substantial property in a fantastic part of Geelong. Blocks like this come to the market only rarely but will undoubtedly appeal to the astute buyer. Definitely worth a closer look.

Description:
GREAT FIRST HOME OR SAVVY INVESTMENT IN GROWING POCKET
This solid brick 3 bed, 1 bath, DLUG, bright and open property set on 535 m2 block will impress.
Set behind a high wooden front fence in the heart of Newcomb this property would suit a young couple starting out with room to grow, or a savvy investor with a rental return of $340 approx p/w.
Comprising of a neat entry and huge open living room with wonderful natural light, solid hard wood floors, split system AC, ceiling fan and a new gas heater for all year round comfort. Located at the front of the home is the master bedroom with BIR, ceiling fan and a lovely leafy garden outlook.
The second bedroom is extra long and spacious and would easily cater for all your bedroom furniture, plus a study space all in one. The 3rd bedroom or 2 living room is located at the rear of the home and is extra-large in size and offers mirrored BIR, AC box and doors leading to the rear yard.
The central kitchen and dining area has been updated and offers great natural light, dishwasher, gas hotplates and wall oven, ample kitchen storage and a dining area seating up to 6.
The main bathroom offers corner shower, vanity storage and heat lamps for those chilly mornings.
Outside you will be delighted with a flat rear yard, undercover pergola section, quality fencing and double lock up garage plus ample parking in the driveway for another 3 cars securely behind the gate. Ideal for storing your boat, campervan or trailer.
This well looked after Newcomb home is a stones throw from local schools, walking distance to nearby Newcomb shopping plaza, 15 mins drive to the coast and less than 2km from Geelong CBD.

Description:
Flexible development - 1447m2 GRZ 2 - 3 street frontages.
Options for ALL demographics:
- Private occupiers - looking for a solid family home with plenty of land and unbeatable capital growth potential to secure your families financial future.
- Investors - wanting the golden triangle of investments. Strong prospect for capital growth / potential high yield / a variety of capital improvement options
- Developers - searching for a multi street fronted residential site. Either retain the house and subdivide multiple allotments with independent titles or clear the site and start from scratch (STCA).
- Commercial venture - with the high profile corner, this site could lend itself to an array of commercial options that can work on residential land including learning centres, medical centres, service stations and more (STCA).
IMPORTANT NOTE: To the North, the bay views are highly unlikely to ever be built out due to the environmental significance of the wetlands and various plans discussed for the land include a golf course and/or mariner.
The residence:
The home itself is a very solid, brick home with sturdy foundation that comprises 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, generous living / dining featuring an open fire place, kitchen with loads of storage, gas cooking and dishwasher, separate laundry and more. A bungalow, plenty of shedding and established trees are added bonuses.
This unique opportunity and exceptional piece of real estate is in a prime location within minutes to the Geelong CBD, Eastern Gardens, waterfront, many schools including daycare/kindergartens, primary and secondary colleges AND multiple shopping villages as well as local shopping strips.
The position is also the gateway to the Bellarine Peninsula offering some of the finest beaches, award winning wineries, historical sites, public and private golf courses, regular markets and events, the Queenscliff/Sorrento ferry to enjoy a day trip on the Mornington Peninsula... AND now with daily ferry trips from Portarlington to Melbourne CBD / Docklands, travel to the world's most liveable city has been made much more convenient.
- General Residential Zone 2 - 1447m2 allotment (approx)
- 3 Street Frontages - giving flexible subdivision options
- Second storey water views to the North - unlikely to ever be built out
- Potential commercial prospect - with high exposure corner
- No easements - giving more land space to develop
Call Dion for further information on 0424 940 629.

Also located within metres of both Portarlington Road and Bellarine Hwy, this position allows easy access to the coast.
Comprising of four bedrooms, living room located at the front of the home, with a lovely outlook to the street, well equipped kitchen, central bathroom, single garage, additional shedding and huge backyard, this property brings with it numerous options for first-home buyers, investors, renovators or developers (STCA) to add value to this property. The home would also be suitable for rental with an estimated return of $320 per week (approx).
This is an amazing opportunity to purchase a substantial sized property less than 3km from the Geelong CBD at absolute entry-level pricing. Dont let this one pass you by.

Description:
Stunning home in underrated locale.
This architectural 60's design, solid double brick property has been completely renovated from floor to ceiling with impeccable taste and contemporary style.
On entry, the quality of the renovation is evident in the attention to detail and quality features. The property comprises 3 bedrooms, plus study or 2nd living or guest bedroom, central bathroom, kitchen, meals, open plan living, separate toilet, laundry and a sensational undercover outdoor entertaining area that will be the envy of your guests. The sleek modern design kitchen features impressive glass splashback behind the 900mm stainless hot plate, range hood and oven, whilst a dishwasher, pantry, plenty of bench space and a breakfast bar with waterfall edges will leave the family chef wanting for nothing. The climate is controlled year round by reverse cycle air conditioning and gas heating.
Outside, the undercover area is the entertainers dream with the spa and elevated deck looking out to the west toward the setting sun.
Additionally, raised vegetable gardens, established fruit trees, manicured garden beds and open spaces are complimented by a lock up garage, storage/workshop and a carport.
The large rear yard also provides plenty of scope for extension or multi dwelling development (STCA), with views available from a second storey west toward Belmont/Highton and north west toward the city.
Take advantage to secure one of the best value homes available in the market place and call Dion today on 0424 940 629 to learn more.
